%% Diagram: Ghostferry three-phase shop migration
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant GF as Ghostferry
    participant SRC as Source pod (MySQL)
    participant DST as Target pod (MySQL)
    participant SH as Sorting Hat
    participant LK as Distributed write lock (Redis)

    Note over GF,DST: Phase 1 — batch copy + binlog tail
    par Batch copy
        GF->>SRC: SELECT rows WHERE shop_id = X
        GF->>DST: INSERT batched rows
    and Binlog stream
        GF->>SRC: Tail binary log, filter shop_id = X
        GF->>DST: Apply matching events
    end

    Note over GF,LK: Phase 2 — cutover (writes paused)
    GF->>LK: Acquire writer lock for shop X
    GF->>SRC: Read final binlog coordinate
    GF->>DST: Apply remaining events up to coordinate
    GF->>GF: Verify row checksums

    Note over SH,DST: Phase 3 — routing flip
    GF->>SH: Update routing table to target pod
    GF->>LK: Release writer lock
    Note over DST: Writes resume against new pod (~2.5s avg downtime)
